Economists and policymakers are well aware of the economic-development benefits at stake Diaspora Africans sent home $48 billion in remittances in 2019.Encouragingly, efforts to increase diaspora investment in innovative African projects are underway. In the United Nations’ 2020 World Investment Report, Secretary-General António Guterres noted that global foreign direct investment (FDI) this year is “expected to fall sharply from 2019 levels of $1.5 trillion” to below the trough it hit during the global financial crisis.
This decline will have a devastating effect on emerging economies, many of which are already in crisis as a result of the Covid-19 pandemic.



